# TDD Test-Driven Development Standards

## Red-Green-Refactor Cycle

```
1. RED     → Write a failing test, specify expected behavior
2. GREEN   → Write minimal code to make the test pass
3. REFACTOR → Clean up code, keeping tests passing
4. Repeat
```

## Test Naming Conventions

### Java

```java
// Format: should_expected_result_when_trigger_condition
@Test
void shouldReturnEligibleForFreeShipping_WhenTotalExceeds100Dollars() {
    // ...
}

@Test
void shouldThrowOrderEmptyException_WhenOrderHasNoLines() {
    // ...
}
```

### TypeScript

```typescript
// Format: should_expected_result_when_trigger_condition
it('should_be_eligible_for_free_shipping_when_total_exceeds_100_dollars', () => {
  // ...
});
```

## Test Structure (AAA Pattern)

```java
class OrderPricingTest {

    @Test
    void shouldCalculateTotalAsSumOfLines() {
        // Arrange: Prepare test data and dependencies
        List<OrderLine> lines = List.of(
            new OrderLine(Money.of(100), 2),
            new OrderLine(Money.of(50), 3)
        );
        Order order = new Order(lines);

        // Act: Execute the operation under test
        Money total = order.totalAmount();

        // Assert: Verify the result
        assertThat(total).isEqualTo(Money.of(350));
    }
}
```

## Unit Testing Principles

### Must Have

- Test one behavior/method
- No dependencies between tests
- Deterministic results (no randomness)
- Fast execution (< 1ms)

### Must NOT Have

- Testing private methods
- Testing implementation details
- Hardcoded expected values
- Accessing external resources (DB/network)

## Mock Usage Principles

### When to Use

- Depending on external services
- Depending on unfinished components
- Need to control system under test boundary

### When NOT to Use

- Fake can be used instead
- Testing real collaboration (e.g., JPA Repository using Testcontainers)

```java
// ✅ Correct: Mock external dependencies
@ExtendWith(MockitoExtension.class)
class OrderServiceTest {

    @Mock
    private PaymentGateway paymentGateway;

    @Mock
    private OrderRepository orderRepository;

    @InjectMocks
    private OrderService orderService;

    @Test
    void shouldProcessPaymentWhenOrderIsPlaced() {
        // Given
        Order order = createValidOrder();
        when(paymentGateway.charge(any())).thenReturn(PaymentResult.success());

        // When
        orderService.placeOrder(order);

        // Then
        verify(paymentGateway).charge(order.getTotalAmount());
        assertThat(order.getStatus()).isEqualTo(OrderStatus.PAID);
    }
}

// ❌ Incorrect: Over-mocking
@Test
void shouldCreateOrder() {
    // Given - Mocked everything, loses meaning
    when(orderRepository.save(any())).thenAnswer(inv -> inv.getArgument(0));
    when(eventPublisher.publish(any())).thenReturn(null);
    when(clock.now()).thenReturn(Instant.now());
}
```

## Test Double Type Selection

| Scenario | Recommended Type | Reason |
|----------|-----------------|--------|
| Fill parameters | Dummy | Parameter not used |
| Simplified implementation | Fake | e.g., InMemoryRepository |
| Pre-configured responses | Stub | Control test data |
| Verify calls | Mock | Verify interactions |
| Retain real + record | Spy | Partial verification |

## Boundary Condition Coverage

```java
@Test
void shouldHandleNullInput() {
    assertThrows(NullPointerException.class, () -> service.process(null));
}

@Test
void shouldHandleEmptyCollection() {
    List<?> result = service.process(List.of());
    assertThat(result).isEmpty();
}

@Test
void shouldHandleMaximumValue() {
    Money result = service.calculate(Money.MAX_VALUE);
    assertThat(result).isEqualTo(Money.MAX_VALUE);
}
```

## TDD Workflow Checklist

### Before Writing Tests

- [ ] Clarify the behavior under test
- [ ] Know the expected output/side effects

### Red Phase

- [ ] Test fails to compile (compile error) or runs failing (assertion failure)
- [ ] Failure message is clear

### Green Phase

- [ ] Write only code to make tests pass
- [ ] Do not write "perfect" code

### Refactor Phase

- [ ] All tests still pass
- [ ] Code is clearer

## Common Mistakes

| Mistake | Symptoms | Correction |
|---------|----------|------------|
| Reverse TDD | Write implementation before tests | Follow Red-Green-Refactor |
| Over-testing | Test all methods | Test behavior, not implementation |
| Weak assertions | `assertTrue(true)` | Precise assertions |
| Slow tests | Unit tests access DB | Mock dependencies |
| Test dependency | Test A depends on Test B state | Tests are independent |
